cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the use of generative networks for providing new image datasets and training classifiers on generated data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the challenges of training machine learning models on unlimited amounts of generated data, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed techniques for improving performance can also be related to the sub-categories of cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
